{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01A82KeDZb8hAJDoTCqnvYcQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `app-user` has:\n- `configure=` (empty/blank) - this means no configure permission\n- `write=.*`\n- `read=.*`\n\nTo declare (create) a queue, `configure` permission is needed. The configure permission pattern needs to match the queue name `app-queue`. Since it's empty, no queues can be declared.\n\nThe fix is to grant `app-user` configure permission on the `/app` vhost. I need to set configure to `.*` (or at least to match `app-queue`).","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":315,"cache_read_input_tokens":30056,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":315},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b7b64a3b-98bb-48b4-8c3e-eb6761e270f0","uuid":"230f70e0-4849-46f8-9c53-a76f5d90bd9a","request_id":"req_011CcdCjfcWZy7evcxmBs6Yo"}
